# Deploy website changes live

This rule applies **only** to the Stress Free Flow **website** repo (`StressFreeFlow_Website` / `jstakich/StressFreeFlowSite`).

Do **not** automatically commit or push changes in the **Stress Free Flow main iOS app** project unless the user explicitly asks.

## Workflow (website only)

After any change to this website, commit and push to `origin/main` without waiting to be asked.

1. Make the requested edit(s) to site files.
2. Commit only relevant files (never `.DS_Store` or secrets).
3. Push to `origin/main` so GitHub Pages updates `stressfreeflow.com`.
4. Tell the user the change is live and suggest a hard refresh if needed.

## Notes

- Website repo: `jstakich/StressFreeFlowSite`
- Live site: `https://stressfreeflow.com`
- Main app: no auto-commit or auto-push unless explicitly requested
- Do not ask "want me to push?" for website changes — pushing live is the default here.
